    <item>
      <title>Career Advice from Terence Tao</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/career-advice/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/career-advice/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/career-advice.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Advice is what we ask for when we already know the answer but wish we didn’t.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erica_Jong&#34;&gt;Erica Jong&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here is my collection of various pieces of advice on academic career issues in mathematics, roughly arranged by the stage of career at which the advice is most pertinent (though of course some of the advice pertains to multiple stages).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Probability of Human Existence Is Infinitesimally Small</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-probability-of-human-existence-is-infinitesimally-small/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Nov 2021 17:53:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-probability-of-human-existence-is-infinitesimally-small/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/the-probability-of-human-existence-is-infinitesimally-small.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://nav.al/existence&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://nav.al/existence&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://nav.al/existence&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-probability-of-human-existence-is-infinitesimally-small&#34;&gt;The Probability of Human Existence Is Infinitesimally Small&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Nov 8 2021&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;From an evolutionary standpoint, it&amp;rsquo;s near impossible&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s another way to think about it that is mathematically frightening for the people who think that the aliens are out there and they&amp;rsquo;re going to visit us sometime in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Every Theory Is Held Inside a Physical Substrate</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 12 Apr 2021 18:06:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://nav.al/substrate&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://nav.al/substrate&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://nav.al/substrate&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate&#34;&gt;Every Theory Is Held Inside a Physical Substrate&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Apr 12 2021&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;re always bound by the laws of physics&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt; There goes my solution for &lt;a href=&#34;&#34;&gt;Zeno&amp;rsquo;s paradox&lt;/a&gt;, which says before you can get all the way somewhere, you have to get halfway there. And before you can get halfway there, you have to get a quarter of the way there, and therefore, you&amp;rsquo;ll never get there.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Foundations Are Math and Logic</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-foundations-are-math-and-logic/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 05 Apr 2019 14:32:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-foundations-are-math-and-logic/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/the-foundations-are-math-and-logic.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://nav.al/math-logic&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://nav.al/math-logic&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://nav.al/math-logic&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-foundations-are-math-and-logic&#34;&gt;The Foundations Are Math and Logic&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Apr 5 2019&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Mathematics and logic are the basis for understanding everything else&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Foundational things are principles, they&amp;rsquo;re algorithms, they&amp;rsquo;re deep seated logical understanding where you can defend it or attack it from any angle. And that&amp;rsquo;s why microeconomics is important because macroeconomics is a lot of memorization, a lot of macro bullshit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Write a rapid prototype first</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/write-a-rapid-prototype-first/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 09:03:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/write-a-rapid-prototype-first/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/write-a-rapid-prototype-first.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/write-a-rapid-prototype-first/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/write-a-rapid-prototype-first/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/write-a-rapid-prototype-first/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;write-a-rapid-prototype-first&#34;&gt;Write a rapid prototype first&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The best performance improvement is the transition from the nonworking state to the working state.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Ousterhout&#34;&gt;John Ousterhout&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Discovering a solution to a mathematical problem is only half of the battle. Actually writing down the argument that you’ve discovered formally can also be a daunting task, especially if the argument is lengthy and is not modeled on an existing one in the literature. While every individual detail of the argument may be clear to the author, the overall structure of the argument may not be immediately obvious. In particular, it is often difficult to make the (important) decisions about the &lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/organise-the-paper/&#34;&gt;organisation of the argument&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/use-good-notation/&#34;&gt;selection of good notation&lt;/a&gt;, until a large part of the paper is already written, at which point any changes in the organisation or in the notation often become painful to implement. (Many times in the past, I have started to write a paper without devoting enough thought to the overall structure, and spent a lot of time establishing some lemmas which I thought were important, only to realise later that one did not actually need the lemma, thus wasting quite a lot of time.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Be patient</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/be-patient/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 19:02:26 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/be-patient/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/be-patient.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-patient/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-patient/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/be-patient/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;be-patient&#34;&gt;Be patient&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If I have ever made any valuable discoveries, it has been owing more to patient attention, than to any other talent.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;— Isaac Newton&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Any given problem generally requires months of effort in order to make satisfactory progress. While it is possible for routine or unexpectedly easy problems to fall within weeks, this is the exception rather than the rule. Thus it is not uncommon for months to pass with no visible progress; however by patiently eliminating fruitless avenues of attack, you are setting things up so that when the breakthrough does come, one can conclude the problem in relatively short order. (But &lt;strong&gt;be sceptical&lt;/strong&gt; of any breakthrough which was &amp;ldquo;too easy&amp;rdquo; and mysteriously failed to address the key difficulty.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Talk to your advisor</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/talk-to-your-advisor/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:59:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/talk-to-your-advisor/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/talk-to-your-advisor.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/talk-to-your-advisor/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/talk-to-your-advisor/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/talk-to-your-advisor/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;talk-to-your-advisor&#34;&gt;Talk to your advisor&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is the province of knowledge to speak and it is the privilege of wisdom to listen.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;(Oliver Wendell Holmes, &amp;ldquo;The Poet at the Breakfast Table&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Your advisor is one of the best sources of guidance you have; not only in directly assisting you with your research topic, but in directing you (both explicitly and implicitly) to relevant researchers, conferences, publications, open problems, folklore, or other pieces of good mathematics. Your advisor also knows your situation well and can give career advice which is tailored to your specific strengths and weaknesses (unlike the &lt;strong&gt;generic advice&lt;/strong&gt; in these pages).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Natural Beauty</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/natural-beauty/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Nov 2005 12:50:39 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/natural-beauty/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/natural-beauty.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://nav.al/natural-beauty&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://nav.al/natural-beauty&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://nav.al/natural-beauty&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://x.com/naval/status/1002103360646823936&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;natural-beauty&#34;&gt;Natural Beauty&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Nov 29 2005&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Looking out of an airplane window, it&amp;rsquo;s quite obvious what structures are natural and what structures are manmade. The natural structures are curvy, chaotic, yet recursive. They take very, very complex patterns and project them to us in a very simple way. The man-made structures are the opposite – they take simple underlying shapes (squares, straight lines, perfect circles) and combine them in haphazard, unpredictable, and hard-to-encode ways. Looking at them is to look at a chaotic jumble of ordered elements.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>在笔记上工作</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/essays/working-on-notes/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Aug 1980 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/essays/working-on-notes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;本文是数学家小平邦彦探讨自己学习和整理数学笔记过程的随笔，分享了他通过反复抄写、重组和思考证明来深化理解数学定理的经历与心得。&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://ts3.tc.mm.bing.net/th/id/OIP-C.ln-kmpIgQQ_lNKcC9gHkvgHaEO?cb=12&amp;amp;rs=1&amp;amp;pid=ImgDetMain&amp;amp;o=7&amp;amp;rm=3&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
